{"parse":{"title":"Buddhapad Hoard","pageid":43343023,"revid":830787754,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">Buddhapad Hoard</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Buddhapad_Hoard_(1)_(BM).JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Buddhapad Hoard (1) (BM).JPG\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG/300px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG\" width=\"300\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG/450px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG/600px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%281%29_%28BM%29.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3000\" data-file-height=\"4000\" /></a><div>Sculpture of the Buddha from the Buddhapad Hoard in the British Museum</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">Material</th><td>\nBronze</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">Created</th><td>\n6th-8th Centuries AD</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">Present location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/British_Museum\" title=\"British Museum\">British Museum</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/London\" title=\"London\">London</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">Registration</th><td>\n1905,1218.1-15</td></tr></tbody></table><p>\nThe <b>Buddhapad Hoard</b> or <i>Buddam Hoard</i> is a large cache of <a href=\"/wiki/Buddhist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Buddhist\">Buddhist</a> sculptures found near the town of <a href=\"/wiki/Buddam,_India\" title=\"Buddam, India\">Buddam</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Andhra_Pradesh\" title=\"Andhra Pradesh\">Andhra Pradesh</a>, southern India. Since 1905, it has formed an important part of the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Museum\" title=\"British Museum\">British Museum</a>'s South Asian collection.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Dating from 6th-8th centuries AD, the style of craftsmanship fuses the northern influences of the <a href=\"/wiki/Gupta_Empire\" title=\"Gupta Empire\">Gupta period</a> with the southern traditions of the <a href=\"/wiki/Deccan_Plateau\" title=\"Deccan Plateau\">Deccan</a>, which in turn greatly influenced Buddhist art in South East Asia in subsequent centuries.\n</p><div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Discovery_and_original_ownership\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Discovery and original ownership</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Discovery_and_original_ownership\">Discovery and original ownership</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Buddhapad_Hoard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Discovery and original ownership\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The hoard was discovered in the late nineteenth century and it was described by the colonial historian <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Sewell_(historian)\" title=\"Robert Sewell (historian)\">Robert Sewell</a> in 1895.<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The artefacts was subsequently donated by the <a href=\"/wiki/Secretary_of_State_for_India\" title=\"Secretary of State for India\">Secretary of State for India</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Museum\" title=\"British Museum\">British Museum</a> in 1905. Given the religious nature of the sculptures, the cache may have originally formed part of a ritual deposit from a Buddhist temple or <a href=\"/wiki/Monastery\" title=\"Monastery\">monastery</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Buddhapad_Hoard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The 6th-8th century hoard<sup id=\"cite_ref-book_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-book-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> is composed of fifteen bronze <a href=\"/wiki/Buddhist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Buddhist\">Buddhist</a> images, the vast majority of which are either statuettes or parts of small figures. There are three relatively intact standing statuettes of the Buddha (the largest of which is 38&#160;cm high), 4 bronze arms, two bases for standing figures (one of which has a <a href=\"/wiki/Brahmi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brahmi\">Brahmi</a> inscription), a representation of the god <a href=\"/wiki/Tirthankara\" title=\"Tirthankara\">Tirthankara</a>, two small Buddha heads, two fragmentary figures of <a href=\"/wiki/Parsvanatha\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Parsvanatha\">Parsvanatha</a> and a bronze model of a <a href=\"/wiki/Stupa\" title=\"Stupa\">stupa</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Buddhapad_Hoard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:30px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Buddhapad_Hoard_(3)_(BM).JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG/120px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG\" width=\"120\" height=\"90\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG/180px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG/240px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%283%29_%28BM%29.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"4000\" data-file-height=\"3000\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Model of a stupa from the hoard\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Buddhapad_Hoard_(2)_(BM).JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG/90px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG/135px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG/180px-Buddhapad_Hoard_%282%29_%28BM%29.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3000\" data-file-height=\"4000\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Bronze statuette of the Buddha with <a href=\"/wiki/Varadamudra\" title=\"Varadamudra\">varadamudra</a> gesture\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Buddhapad_Hoard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Zwalf W, Buddhism: Art and Faith, London, British Museum</li>\n<li>Barrett D, Studies in Indian Sculpture and Painting, London</li>\n<li>R. Fisher, Buddhist art and architecture (London, Thames &amp; Hudson, 1993)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Buddhapad_Hoard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.britishmuseum.org/research/collection_online/search.aspx?place=40193&amp;plaA=40193-3-2\">British Museum Collection</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-book-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-book_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Baptiste, John Guy&#160;; with essays by Pierre; Becker, Lawrence; Bellina, B\u00e9r\u00e9nice; Brown, Robert L.; Ca